---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: About / Contact
metaDescription: Learn about WPCNA, monthly meetings, and how to contact the White Plains Council of Neighborhood Associations.
pageClass: page-about
---
{% from "components/macros.njk" import resourceCard %}
<section class="page-hero page-hero--compact">
  <div class="container page-hero__content">
    <p class="eyebrow">About WPCNA</p>
    <h1>A clearer civic front door for White Plains neighborhoods</h1>
    <p>{{ site.mission }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--flush-top">
  <div class="container about-grid">
    <article class="about-copy">
      <h2>Citywide role</h2>
      <p>WPCNA connects neighborhood associations and residents with one another, with city processes, and with the local institutions that shape everyday life in White Plains.</p>
      <p>This public-facing site is designed to answer the basics quickly: what is happening, when it is happening, where it is, and what to do next.</p>

      <h2 id="meetings">Meetings and participation</h2>
      <p>{{ site.meetingNote }}</p>
      <p>Residents and neighborhood leaders can use the agendas archive to track issues, follow upcoming meetings, and stay aligned with current priorities.</p>
      <p><a class="text-link" href="https://wp-cna.org/agendas" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Open the agendas archive</a></p>

      <h2>Neighborhood focus</h2>
      <p>White Plains works best when citywide activity and neighborhood context are visible together. WPCNA helps keep both in view without turning the site into a cluttered archive.</p>
    </article>

    <div class="about-sidebar">
      <figure class="about-photo">
        <img src="{{ site.aboutImage | withPrefix }}" alt="{{ site.aboutImageAlt }}" loading="lazy">
      </figure>

      <aside class="detail-card">
        <p class="eyebrow">Contact</p>
        <h2>{{ site.contactName }}</h2>
        <p>{{ site.name }}</p>
        <p>{{ site.location }}</p>
        <p><a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a></p>
        <a class="button button--block" href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">Email WPCNA</a>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--tint">
  <div class="container section__intro">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Useful Links</p>
      <h2>Official pages residents may need</h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="container resource-grid">
    {% for resource in resources %}
      {{ resourceCard(resource) }}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
